# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# SECRETS ONLY for the agent-worker container (the LLM dependency judge).
#   cd deploy && cp agent.env.example agent.env   # agent.env is gitignored
#
# SETTINGS (provider / model / output_mode / base_url) are NOT set here — they
# live in config/agent.yml, which is mounted live into the container:
# edit the YAML, then `docker compose -f docker-compose.services.yml restart agent`.
#
# Uncomment exactly the key your config/agent.yml provider needs. The default
# provider (ollama) needs NO key — with it this file can be absent entirely.
#
# Why a separate file (not deploy/.env): .env only feeds compose ${...}
# interpolation and never reaches containers by itself, while this file is
# injected wholesale into the agent container only — so the judge gets exactly
# its own secret and none of the stack's. See deploy/README.md.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# provider: openai-api          (also set NORN_AGENT_BASE_URL= empty in deploy/.env —
#                                the compose Ollama default must not leak into OpenAI)
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...

# provider: openai-oauth        (bearer flow: docs/guide/agent/README.md)
# NORN_OPENAI_OAUTH_TOKEN=...

# provider: openrouter
# OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-...

# provider: anthropic-api
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
